+Let $c^*, \hat c \in \calC$ be two distinct challenges with $c^* \ne \hat c$. For any signer~$i$, let $c_i^{*\prime}$ and $\hat c_i'$ be the ternary polynomials reconstructed from $(c^*, \bvec{b}_i^*)$ and $(\hat c, \hat{\bvec{b}}_i)$ respectively. Then $\Delta c_i' = c_i^{*\prime} - \hat c_i'$ has coefficients in $\{-2,-1,0,1,2\}$ and satisfies $\norm{\Delta c_i'} \le 2\sqrt{\kappa}$.
