+\begin{lemma}[Non-zero forked challenge difference]\label{lem:nonzero}
+With the notation above, $\Delta c_i' \neq \bvec{0}$ for every signer~$i$.
 \end{lemma}
+\begin{proof}
+Each reconstructed ternary polynomial $c_i'$ has support exactly equal to the support of the corresponding binary challenge~$c$ and satisfies $c_i' \equiv c \pmod 2$ coefficientwise. Since $c^* \neq \hat c$ in~$\calC$, their supports differ at some coefficient position~$j$. At that position, one of $c_i^{*\prime}$ and $\hat c_i'$ has coefficient $\pm 1$ while the other has coefficient~$0$, so $\Delta c_i'$ is non-zero.
+\end{proof}
 
